---
description: Remind agents to consider LLM token cost when generating or refactoring code
alwaysApply: true
---

When generating, reviewing, or refactoring code in this workspace:

- Prefer concise implementations that minimize token count without sacrificing readability.
- Avoid duplicating large blocks of code — extract shared logic into functions.
- Remove unused imports, dead code, and commented-out blocks before presenting results.
- When suggesting file inclusions for AI context, prioritize files with the highest signal-to-token ratio.
- If a file exceeds 500 lines, suggest splitting it before adding more code.
- Flag any generated code that would add more than 200 tokens of boilerplate (e.g. verbose type declarations that could use inference).
